Description: Body sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery amphora; white slip; exterior: from top, part of dividing band consisting of painted dot and billet pattern; below, part of painted lotus bud and lotus flower frieze with added purple on lozenge and lotus bud; interior surface very worn.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (Pl. GB 581, 5)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.085)
